{"TopicId":193905,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Jeb\u0026#039;s Locomotive, now with working running gear!","CreatedByName":"Jamie Logan","CreatedById":67916,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-15T20:50:50Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jamie Logan","CreatedById":67916,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-15T20:50:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:36px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003EHowdy, Y\u0027all.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003EWay back in ye old days of 2013 KSP, a younger and perhaps less-skilled me tried his hand at building a steam locomotive replica. This was the result:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022YWPVb30.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/YWPVb30.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002267916\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3450743611\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/55692-jebs-locomotive-stock-old-fashioned-train-replica/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:212px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003ENot too shabby, given the limited part repository at the time. Though I\u0027ve seen many KSP players build fantastic train replicas, I had yet to come across one that utilized the new stock robotics parts to make working running gear. So, I set out to overhaul Jeb\u0027s once-mighty steamer with the latest in Kerbal engineering technology:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00229IkUHxK.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002255.52\u0022 height=\u0022568\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/9IkUHxK.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003EJeb\u0027s Locomotive was designed to function in a similar fashion as typical modern locomotive replicas do; the running gear is powered by the drive wheels which are in turn powered by electric motors, instead of steam power driving the running gear and subsequently driving the wheels. The 6 rover wheels only provide brakes and steering, while the 6 rotor wheels are coupled in axle pairs using standard docking ports to provide side-to-side consistency in operation. The running gear is largely coupled together using junior docking ports. \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003EEngine power is controlled using the KAL controller in the cab. Press action group 1 to engage the drive motors and start up the fuel cells, set the controller to play until you reach your desired speed, then pause it. The play speed is set slow intentionally, as sometimes sudden changes to the RPM can mess up the running gear synchronicity. Unfortunately, the engine plates used to make the drive wheels don\u0027t have great traction with the ground (leading to slight slipping), and collision tolerances will limit your top speed to \u0026lt;9 m/s (as you will see shortly). You can of course go faster by disabling crash damage on the debug menu, but beware that at higher speeds the running gear can easily go out of whack. I find it runs quite nicely around 6-7 m/s surface speed. \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003EYou are welcome to download and add on things like coal cars, passenger cars, etc. if you\u0027d like. The locomotive is already 218 parts as-is, so expect lag if you\u0027re planning on adding a lot to it. If anything, download it just to drive it up to 9 m/s, for funzies. \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003EThe entire vessel is Stock \u002B DLC. \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003EDownload: \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Jamie_Logan/Jebs-Locomotive\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Jamie_Logan/Jebs-Locomotive\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003EHere is a gif of the running gear in motion at a slow speed: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/bHYKT1b.gifv\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://i.imgur.com/bHYKT1b.gifv\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003EGallery:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022BBeKL7m.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002255.31\u0022 height=\u0022566\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/BBeKL7m.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022fheszbD.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002255.31\u0022 height=\u0022566\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/fheszbD.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022xzKFhQl.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002255.31\u0022 height=\u0022566\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/xzKFhQl.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022UvMWhmg.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002255.31\u0022 height=\u0022566\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/UvMWhmg.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00222Nps0Ll.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002255.31\u0022 height=\u0022566\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/2Nps0Ll.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XAQRtsQ.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002255.31\u0022 height=\u0022566\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/XAQRtsQ.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022zH3BFgO.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002255.31\u0022 height=\u0022566\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/zH3BFgO.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022EVmITDz.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002255.31\u0022 height=\u0022566\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/EVmITDz.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003EI\u0027M GOIN\u0027 OFF THE RAILS ON A... oh nevermind.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Times New Roman\u0027, Times, serif;\u0022\u003EI hope you liked it! Check out my last build too:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00224W0s15l.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002255.63\u0022 height=\u0022569\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/4W0s15l.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002267916\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8561830337\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/193850-hummingbyrd-vtol-personnel-dropship/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:212px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-05-25T21:17:51Z\u0022 title=\u002205/25/2020 09:17  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMay 25, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Jamie Logan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-15T21:13:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat may be the best looking locomotive I have seen.\u00A0 I did a doubletake when I realized it was stock only.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-05-15T21:13:52Z\u0022 title=\u002205/15/2020 09:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMay 15, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Klapaucius\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jamie Logan","CreatedById":67916,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-15T21:17:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223785859\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193905\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221589577199\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181256\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Klapaucius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Klapaucius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat may be the best looking locomotive I have seen.\u00A0 I did a doubletake when I realized it was stock only.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}